HEADWORD: Otheoscope
<hw>O"the*o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'wqei^n</grk> to push + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for exhibiting the repulsive
action produced by light or heat in an exhausted vessel; a modification
of the radiometer.</def> <rj><au>W. Crookes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

